- Roles:

    cmd_role 'role_name' => (
        abbrev  => 1,
        optargs => sub {
        },
    );

    subcmd 'App::foo::bar' => (
        with    => 'role_name',
        optargs => sub {

            # cmd specific
        },
    );

- Do not inherit options from parent commands?

- Immediate response/trigger to a particular option

    opt version => (
        isa     => 'Boo',
        comment => 'display version string and exit',
        on_set  => sub {
            my ($cmd,$value) = @_;
            print "Version $VERSION\n";
            exit;
        },
    );


- An Enum type
    opt things => (
        isa     => 'Enum',
        valid   => [qw/one two three/],
        comment => 'only allows set values',
    );


- Currently using new type 'Boo' but how about 'Flag'?
